[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     50[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Configuration and Constants
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     51[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     52[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Everything that is configuration rather than logic lives here. Resource names, the unit map, the unit capacities, the overflow rules, the per-source inflow rates, the unit-assignment probability table, the discharge-hour-of-day pattern, the survival-model hazard parameters, and the Monte Carlo settings are what you would change between environments.
