[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1526[0m:[38;5;10m[49m === Operational signals ===
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1527[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   gridlock_unit_hours:    N
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1528[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   tight_unit_hours:       M
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1529[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   mean_overflow_residual: 0.X
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1530[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   per_unit_max_util:      {'ed-hold': '...', 'tele-3-east': '...', ...}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1531[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1532[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1533[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A real pipeline against a single hospital with 5 to 30 units, 200 to 600 active encounters, and 500 to 1000 Monte Carlo samples runs the inference cycle in tens of seconds on a small Lambda or AWS Batch job, produces the same shape of output, and writes the records straight to a real DynamoDB table that the bed huddle dashboard queries every few seconds.
